  "body": "#5072 replaced the static accessor to `Thread::currentThreadId()` with a [ThreadFactory](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/include/envoy/thread/thread.h#L38) that exposes a virtual [currentThreadId()](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/include/envoy/thread/thread.h#L51) function.\r\n\r\nThis new approach to obtaining the current thread's ID introduces a significant hurdle to writing thread safety assertions (e.g., `ASSERT(owner_thread_id_ == staticGetCurrentThreadId())`), since the `ThreadFactory` instance must now be accessible to classes implementing such assertions.\r\n\r\nI explored making the `ThreadFactory` available via the `Singleton::Manager`, but there is a [circular dependency](https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/singleton/manager_impl.h#L18) that prevents a simple/clean change to expose it as a singleton.",
